The '''Frink Medal for British Zoologists''' is awarded by the [[Zoological Society of London]] "For significant and original contributions by a professional zoologist to the development of zoology."<ref>{{cite web| title=ZSL Awards| url=http://www.zsl.org/science/scientific-awards/| access-date=26 April 2015|publisher=Zoological Society of London}}</ref> {{#tag:ref|The award for a particular year is presented to the recipient the following year. This can lead to discrepancies in some sources over the year of an award, with some reporting the year of presentation and some reporting the year stated on the award.|group="n"}} It consists of a bronze plaque (76 by 83 millimetres),<ref>{{cite book|last=Jones|first=Mark|year=1986|title=Contemporary British Medals|page=40}}</ref> depicting a bison and carved by British sculptor [[Elisabeth Frink]].<ref name="Gardiner">{{cite book|last=Gardiner|first=Stephen|year=1998|title=Frink: The Official Biography of Elisabeth Frink|page=198}}</ref> The Frink Medal was instituted in 1973 and first presented in 1974.<ref name="Gardiner"/>

